Additional Note: Our box fits directly behind the front console and extends over the rear bench for increased volume. As an added bonus, the top of the box serves as a great armrest for the rear passengers--or mount your amp on top if you like. The box fits perfectly in the space provided and is designed to lock itself into place, but can also be easily moved if needed. This box is a down fire box meaning the sub faces the floor. What this means is that your bass will reflect off the floor for an even greater bass response. There is 2" of clearance between the baffle and the hump, so no worries about your sub contacting the floor. This setup is not only a solid performer but is also very stealthy since the woofer cannot be seen.
